- 2.0.1 | Feb 19 2026:
[New] README.md Markdown version for GitHub rendering (README.md)
[Change] README expanded with Docker compat, ipset, GRE tunnel, and IPv6
      documentation; grammar and structure fixes throughout (README)
[New] External INPUT/OUTPUT rule preservation in DOCKER_COMPAT mode;
      save_external_baseline() captures non-APF rules before flush,
      restore_external_baseline() replays them after flush; protects
      Docker Swarm, kube-proxy, and Calico CNI rules from being
      destroyed during APF start/restart/stop (functions.apf)
[New] Docker compat external INPUT preservation tests: 3 tests covering
      start, flush, and restart scenarios with simulated Docker Swarm
      INPUT rule (tests/20-docker-compat.bats)
[Change] DOCKER_COMPAT conf.apf comment updated to document INPUT/OUTPUT
      preservation alongside FORWARD and nat (conf.apf)
[New] Docker/container chain preservation mode (DOCKER_COMPAT); when enabled,
      flush() only removes APF-owned chains, preserving Docker, containerd,
      Kubernetes, and Podman chains in FORWARD and nat table. Fast load and
      snapshot save automatically disabled in compat mode to prevent
      iptables-restore from overwriting external chains (conf.apf,
      functions.apf, apf, .ca.def)
[New] flush_apf_chains() surgical flush function; removes only known APF
      chains from filter table, flushes mangle PREROUTING/POSTROUTING,
      resets INPUT/OUTPUT policies while leaving FORWARD policy and nat/raw
      tables untouched (functions.apf)
[New] Docker compat test suite: 10 tests covering chain preservation across
      start/flush/restart, nuclear flush default, fast load skip, mangle vs
      nat behavior (tests/20-docker-compat.bats)
[Fix] flush_apf_chains() IPv6 chain list missing PHP, DSHIELD, SDROP;
      these dual-stack chains (created via ipt -N) were cleaned from IPv4
      but left as orphans in ip6tables when DOCKER_COMPAT=1 and USE_IPV6=1,
      causing -N errors on subsequent start (functions.apf)
[Fix] GRE eval command injection: create_gretun() no longer uses eval to
      build the tunnel command; replaced with direct $ip tunnel add using
      if/else for the optional key flag (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] allow_hosts()/deny_hosts() glob expansion: all 8 for-in-$(cat) loops
      converted to while IFS= read -r with process substitution, eliminating
      glob expansion risk on trust file entries (functions.apf)
[Fix] DLIST disabled regression: dlist_php(), dlist_dshield(), and
      dlist_spamhaus() else branches now clear the rules file when the feature
      is disabled; previously restored from backup, contradicting operator
      intent to disable the list (functions.apf)
[Fix] --gre-down leaves stale firewall chains: gre_teardown() now flushes
      and deletes GRE_IN/GRE_OUT chains and removes INPUT/OUTPUT jumps;
      previously only destroyed tunnel interfaces (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] --gre-up idempotent: gre_init() now guards chain creation with
      existence check; previously failed with "chain already exists" when
      called on a running firewall (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] --ipset-update mutex: the --ipset-update CLI path now calls
      mutex_lock() to prevent racing with concurrent apf -r (apf)
[Fix] GRE tunnel creation exit codes: $ip tunnel add and $ip link set
      return codes now checked; failure aborts with error message instead
      of continuing to add firewall rules for non-existent interfaces
      (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] GRE endpoint validation: create_gretun() now uses valid_ip_cidr()
      instead of valid_host() for routefrom/routeto; GRE requires IP
      addresses, not hostnames which the kernel silently rejects
      (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] GRE key validation: tunnel key now validated as integer; non-numeric
      values rejected with error message before reaching the kernel
      (gretunnel.sh)
[New] MCAST6 NDP RETURN test assertion: verifies ICMPv6 RETURN exemptions
      in MCAST6 chain that protect NDP from multicast blocking
      (tests/06-ipv6.bats)
[New] DLIST disabled no-chain test: verifies DLIST_*=0 clears rules files
      and creates no iptables chain (tests/19-dlist.bats)
[Fix] GRE protocol 47 test assertions widened for old iptables on Ubuntu
      12.04 which displays -p 47 instead of -p gre (tests/18-gre.bats)
[Fix] DShield /24 host inflation: dlist_dshield() no longer appends /24
      to individual host IPs from the DShield feed; entries are now written
      as-is, preventing collateral blocking of 256 addresses per host
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] dlist download resilience: dlist_dshield(), dlist_php(), and
      dlist_spamhaus() now backup rules files before download and restore
      from backup on failure; previously a failed download left rules files
      empty, losing all existing entries (functions.apf)
[Change] dlist parse-time validation: dlist_dshield(), dlist_php(), and
      dlist_spamhaus() now validate entries via valid_ip_cidr() during
      parsing; garbage from corrupted downloads is rejected before writing
      to rules files (functions.apf)
[Fix] conf.apf and .ca.def DShield description corrected from "top
      networks" to "top hosts" to match actual feed content (conf.apf,
      .ca.def)
[New] DLIST chain-loading test suite: 11 tests covering DSHIELD/PHP/SDROP
      chain creation, DROP rules, INPUT attachment, backup/restore
      resilience, and invalid entry rejection (tests/19-dlist.bats)
[Change] Subsystem definition file naming normalized: gre.conf renamed to
      gre.rules for consistency with ipset.rules and other .rules files;
      all references updated (gretunnel.sh, conf.apf, .ca.def, tests)
[Change] ipset.rules and gre.rules headers now cross-reference their
      conf.apf config sections for discoverability
[Fix] importconf now preserves gre.rules during upgrades; previously
      user tunnel definitions were lost on upgrade (importconf)
[New] GRE tunnel support: encapsulated point-to-point links with dedicated
      GRE_IN/GRE_OUT chains, protocol 47 rules, and per-tunnel interface
      accept rules. USE_GRE config toggle, gre.rules definition file,
      create_gretun()/destroy_gretun()/gre_init()/gre_flush()/gre_teardown()/
      gre_status() lifecycle functions, --gre-up/--gre-down/--gre-status CLI
      options, auto-MTU calculation, keepalive, tunnel key, per-tunnel
      overrides, source/target role routing (conf.apf, internals.conf,
      gretunnel.sh, gre.rules, firewall, functions.apf, apf, .ca.def)
[New] GRE test suite: 14 tests covering tunnel creation, chain structure,
      protocol 47 rules, interface rules, addresses, MTU, IP routing,
      disable/enable, flush persistence, teardown, validation
      (tests/18-gre.bats)
[Change] All 10 Dockerfiles and install-apf.sh updated with USE_GRE="0"
      config override for deterministic test behavior
[New] ipset block list support: kernel-level hash tables for O(1) IP matching.
      USE_IPSET config toggle, ipset.rules definition file, ipset_load()/
      ipset_update()/ipset_flush() lifecycle functions, --ipset-update CLI
      option for cron hot-reload, cron.d.apf_ipset cron job, ip_set/xt_set
      module loading, check_deps() ipset warning (conf.apf, internals.conf,
      functions.apf, bt.rules, apf, install.sh, ipset.rules, cron.d.apf_ipset)
[New] ipset test suite: 12 tests covering set creation, chain attachment,
      match rules, hot-reload, flush cleanup, empty/CIDR blocklists, logging
      (tests/17-ipset.bats)
[Change] All 10 Dockerfiles updated with ipset package and USE_IPSET="0"
      config override for deterministic test behavior
[Change] CentOS 6 and Ubuntu 12.04 added to GitHub Actions CI matrix
      (.github/workflows/smoke-test.yml)
[Change] Makefile test-all and test-all-parallel targets now include
      centos6 and ubuntu1204 (tests/Makefile)
[Fix] ipset entry count assertions use portable member counting for
      old ipset v6.x compatibility on CentOS 6 and Ubuntu 12.04
      (tests/17-ipset.bats)
[Fix] importconf now preserves ipset.rules during upgrades (importconf)
[Fix] MCAST6 chain now exempts NDP ICMPv6 types 133-136 before blocking
      ff00::/8; previously BLK_MCATNET=1 with USE_IPV6=1 broke IPv6
      neighbor discovery by dropping multicast NDP packets (bt.rules)
[Fix] SSH helper removed dead rule with mutually exclusive --syn and
      --state ESTABLISHED,RELATED flags that could never match (firewall)
[Fix] SSH helper removed spurious UDP ACCEPT rule — SSH is TCP-only;
      rule incorrectly opened UDP on the SSH port (firewall)
[Fix] Interface validation error messages now reference the specific
      failing interface instead of the entire interface list (firewall)
[Change] ipset chain wiring uses ipt4() helper instead of raw $IPT for
      consistency with dual-stack convention (functions.apf)
[Change] Loopback rules use ipt() helper and remove redundant 0/0 source/
      destination match (firewall)
[Fix] Advanced trust syntax now rejects entries with unrecognized flow,
      direction, or protocol fields instead of passing them as raw
      iptables flags — prevents malformed trust entries from injecting
      arbitrary arguments (functions.apf)
[Fix] refresh() temp files now use mktemp instead of PID-based naming,
      preventing symlink attack vectors (functions.apf)
[Fix] dlist_ecnshame() download now filters for IP-shaped content and
      strips comments, matching all other dlist download functions
      (functions.apf)
[Change] All dlist_*_hosts() chain-loading functions, dnet(), expirebans(),
      and refresh() converted from for-in-cat to while-read loops,
      eliminating glob expansion risk on trust file entries (functions.apf)
[Fix] valid_host() IPv4 now delegates to valid_ip_cidr() for octet range
      validation; rejects invalid addresses like 999.1.2.3 and masks > /32
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] valid_host() IPv6 CIDR mask now validated <= 128; rejects invalid
      masks like /999 (functions.apf)
[Fix] valid_host() IPv6 regex accepts compressed forms starting with ::
      (e.g. ::1, ::/0); leading hextet changed from {1,4} to {0,4}
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] Fast load with USE_IPV6=1 falls through to full load when
      ip6tables-restore is missing instead of silently succeeding
      with only IPv4 rules loaded (apf)
[Fix] IPv6 tests skip gracefully when ip6tables kernel module is unavailable;
      adds ip6tables_available() helper and per-test skip guards across 6
      test files for GH Actions CentOS 7 compatibility; fixed BATS subprocess
      isolation issue with variable-based skip (tests/helpers/assert-iptables.bash,
      tests/04-trust-system.bats, tests/06-ipv6.bats, tests/08-fastload.bats,
      tests/09-flush-cleanup.bats, tests/11-advanced-trust.bats,
      tests/16-dependency-check.bats)
